			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-5" style="font-family: var(--font-sans); color: var(--color-muted);">
					<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">The gospel is the good news that God is a loving Father who made you, came after you when you were lost, and through His Son Jesus&rsquo; death and resurrection brings you home as His own beloved child.</strong> The word itself simply means <em>good news</em> &mdash; an announcement of something that has already happened, not advice about something you must achieve. And the news is better than most people have been told. It is not mainly that you can avoid hell or earn a place in heaven; it is that the God who seemed distant is a Father, and He has done everything required to welcome His children back to Himself. Jesus called Himself &ldquo;the way&rdquo; &mdash; and the destination He named was not a place but a Person: the Father. Understand that, and the whole Bible reads as one long rescue story with your name in it.
				</p>

				<aside class="my-7 px-6 py-5 rounded-2xl" style="background-color: #fdf2f5; border: 1px solid #f9d6e0;">
					<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-2" style="color: var(--color-brand); font-family: var(--font-sans);">Key takeaway</p>
					<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="font-family: var(--font-serif); color: var(--color-ink);">The gospel is good news, not good advice: God is a Father who, through His Son&rsquo;s death and resurrection, brings His lost children home. The destination was always the Father Himself.</p>
				</aside>

				<nav aria-label="On this page" class="my-8 px-5 py-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: var(--color-surface-low); border: 1px solid var(--color-hairline);">
					<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color: var(--color-muted); font-family: var(--font-sans);">On this page</p>
					<ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-5 gap-y-2 list-none m-0 p-0 text-sm" style="font-family: var(--font-sans);">
